HEADWORD: hectogram
<hw>hec"to*gram</hw> <pr>(h⟦ecr⟧k"t⟦osl⟧*gr⟦acr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>hectogramme</ets>, fr. Gr. <grk>'ekato`n</grk> hundred +
F. <ets>gramme</ets> a gram.]</ety> <def>A measure of mass or weight,
containing a hundred grams, or about 3.527 ounces avoirdupois. See 3rd
<er>gram</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
